    <note type="biography">
        <p>Brewer. Head of Barclay, Perkins &amp; Co., brewers. Built an observatory at Bury Hill near Dorking, Surrey, 1848. Paralysed, 1855. Grandson of Robert Barclay (1751–1830), who established a large collection of exotic plants in the gardens at Bury Hill. FRS 1852.</p></note>
